Hi Malini – sorry for the late reply! Unit tests are small, automated tests written to verify that individual pieces of code (functions or classes) work as expected. We write them before or alongside development to catch bugs early and ensure our code remains reliable as we make changes.
Hi Sanchith, just following up—are you available for a call to discuss the DSU program pathway data setup? Let me know a time that works for you.
